metadata.name: The Fringe #69
metadata.description:
We are innately aware of our bodies' position through perception of space. If we are visibly surrounded by walls with flooring under, a ceiling above, and a window facing the sky, we know we are inside of an enclosed space, with a view of outside. But how does a room stopped being an enclosed space? Can a space with 3 walls be considered a room? If we are surrounded by walls but our ceiling is gone, then are we inside or outside? This is an exploration on the edges of our ability to perceive space. The fringes that instill some fear in our mind. And that fear is failing to make sense of our position in a space that slowly loses its tangibility.

------------
Press [s] to save captured image
------------
It may take a few seconds to render, depending on the device.

created using WEBGL on p5.js
dirbots - Jan23

metadata.name: Missplaced #77
metadata.description:
Being in a space, knowing that we are enveloped by an object‚Äîa ground or a wall‚Äîmade us aware of our external reality. And when a space gains social, cultural, or emotional meaning, it becomes a place.

But sometimes, these spaces and places betray us, isolating the inhabitants who live in them, as if every room and ground are turning hostile and apathetic to the beings who live within its own walls.

In the end, as a way to confirm our being, we are wired to belong to a place, whether it's a theoretical place or a physical place. This feeling of being misplaced can happen even in the most hospitable places in the universe.

------------
11 Color Palette
4 Variant of "Home"
4 Variant of "Environment"
and some Planetary

metadata.name: Radiant #21
metadata.description:
We were all born with a jewel in our heart ‚Äì golden, shining.  Maybe you call it love, or the divine, or beauty.  The trials of life can cover up that jewel, and make it hard to see the beauty within.  We think we‚Äôre not worthy, not lovable.  But that‚Äôs a lie.  The jewel is always there.  You just need to clean off the gunk.  We are all made of love and supernovas.  You always were, and always will be - radiant.

Radiant was created generatively in p5.js.  Seven possible radial designs overlap on two canvases. On the top canvas, circles or arcs are erased to reveal the canvas below. There are four ways the background gets created, mostly using Perlin noise to pick colors from the palette. There are 34 hand-crafted palettes of 7 colors each. 

Original pixel density 1 with grain added automatically.
After pressing ‚Äúopen‚Äù:
2 ‚Äì 5 to increase pixel density.  
g to add grain.  Adding grain takes a while at pixel density 5.
s to save a png.
Screen resize renders at pixel density 1.

I love sharing what I‚Äôve learned about gen art and inspiring others on my YouTube channel, Steve‚Äôs Makerspace. Follow me there and on Twitter @stevemakerspace and Mastodon @stevesmakerspace.

metadata.name: Skravert #130
metadata.description:
‚ÄòSkravert‚Äô - Norwegian, verb, past tense. ‚ÄòThe act of filling an area with lines; to shade an area‚Äô.

Skravert is a series of 320 sketches, each capturing the texture and feel of a material residing somewhere between cardboard and woolen rugs. The project is centred around rectangle subdivision and a line drawing algorithm, giving each piece its own unique expression when combined with a selection of 28 different color  palettes.  

Original artwork by perkwerk * made with p5.js * 2021

metadata.name: NESTED IDENTITIES #131
metadata.description:
Nested identities redact fingerprints but deeper meaning can still be found.

Nested identifies refers to the idea that a person may have multiple identities that are interconnected and interdependent. These identities may be related to a person's cultural background, ethnicity, nationality, gender, sexual orientation, social class, profession, and other factors. It is possible that a person may want to conceal or redact certain aspects of their identity in order to protect their privacy or to avoid discrimination or persecution. However, even if certain details about a person's identity are hidden or redacted, it may still be possible to infer deeper meaning or understand more about their experiences and perspectives based on the context in which they express themselves and the information that is available.


The concept of nested identities highlights the complexity and multifaceted nature of a person's identity, and how different aspects of identity can intersect and influence each other. It is important to recognize and respect the diversity of identities that people may hold, and to be mindful of the ways in which power dynamics and social context can shape how people present and express their identities. It is also important to recognize that people's identities may evolve and change over time, and that everyone has the right to self-identify and to define their own identity on their own terms.

Press p to download a high quality export.

metadata.name: SNOWMENZ #23
metadata.description:
Welcome to my winter drop. This time, I've decided to bring some nostalgia to the table with a snowmen themed collection. As a nod to my previous RAGGEDZ collection featuring scarecrows, I've put a spooky twist on the classic winter icon.

Each snowmen NFT will be unique and terrifying, with randomly generated elements including a hat, eyes, nose, body decoration, arms, an overlay, and a background. The arms, in particular, will be separate to break up the symmetry and add even more variety to the collection.

Don't let the frosty exterior fool you, these snowmen are not to be trifled with. Happy collecting!

Made using PureSpider's fxhash template üñ§

The secret to happiness is to simplify as much as possible. The details surrounding us must be said goodbye as soon as possible. metadata.name: Moonlit Native Bush #57
metadata.description:
Moonlit Native Bush with Fog is a dense forest scene that uses shaders to achieve effects that would be difficult or impossible in plain p5js.

The moon, corona, grain, and fog are rendered in a shader. The shader slows the rendering a little, but considering the effects it can achieve, it's not much.

The moon color is one of the palette colors with the luminance toned down to a reasonable level. The fog color is the moon color mixed with some white to shade it just a touch. 

Moonlit Native Bush is responsive and looks great on any size display up to 4K, but may take some time to render on very large screens.

Since Moonlit Native Bush uses shaders, a decent gpu is recommended.

Variations:

- 41 palettes and small drop means a big chance of getting a unique palette.
- All layouts unique
- Fog Intensity
- Fog Speed X
- Fog SpeedY
- Moon Size
- Moon Blur
- Graininess

'f' toggles the fog.
'a' toggles the animation.
